# Pet Store API

A simple pet store API example

HOST: https://api.petstore.example.com/v1

## Group Pets

## /pets [/pets]

### List all pets [GET]

Returns a list of all pets in the store

+ Parameters
    + limit (optional, integer) - Maximum number of pets to return

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "pets": [
                {
                    "id": 1,
                    "name": "Fluffy",
                    "species": "cat"
                },
                {
                    "id": 2,
                    "name": "Buddy",
                    "species": "dog"
                }
            ]
        }

### Create a pet [POST]

Add a new pet to the store

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "age": 3,
            "name": "Max",
            "species": "dog"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "age": 3,
            "id": 3,
            "name": "Max",
            "species": "dog"
        }

## Group Pets

## /pets/{petId} [/pets/{petId}]

### Get pet by ID [GET]

Returns details of a specific pet

+ Parameters
    + petId (required, integer) - ID of the pet to retrieve

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "age": 2,
            "id": 1,
            "name": "Fluffy",
            "species": "cat"
        }

+ Response 404

    Pet not found

### Update a pet [PUT]

Update an existing pet's information

+ Parameters
    + petId (required, integer)

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "age": 3,
            "name": "Fluffy Updated"
        }

+ Response 200

    Pet updated successfully

### Delete a pet [DELETE]

Remove a pet from the store

+ Parameters
    + petId (required, integer)

+ Response 204

    Pet deleted successfully

+ Response 404

    Pet not found

